  "title": "Accessing Shared Network Drives and File Shares",
  "question": "How do I access shared network drives and file shares?",
  "answer": "Windows: Step 1 - Click on the 'File Explorer' icon on your taskbar. Step 2 - In the left pane, select 'This PC'. Step 3 - Click on the 'Computer' tab at the top, then select 'Map network drive'. Step 4 - Choose a drive letter and enter the folder path (e.g., \\servername\sharename). Step 5 - Check 'Reconnect at sign-in' if you want to access it automatically in the future, then click 'Finish'. Step 6 - If prompted, enter your network credentials in the format 'DOMAIN\\username' and your password. macOS: Step 1 - Open 'Finder' from the dock. Step 2 - In the menu bar, click 'Go' and select 'Connect to Server'. Step 3 - Enter the server address (e.g., smb://servername/sharename) in the 'Server Address' field. Step 4 - Click 'Connect'. Step 5 - If prompted, enter your network credentials in the format 'DOMAIN\\username' and your password. Step 6 - Choose the shared folder you want to access and click 'OK'. You should now see the shared drive in your Finder sidebar or File Explorer."
